The Sudeten Germans in 1945 asked to include Umava in the United States.
This is the result of the letter deposited in the Scientific Library of South Bohemia.
If we cannot be part of Germany or Austria, we want to live at least under the patronage of the United States.
With this desire, it is said, some groups of Sudeten Germans turned in 1945 to the President of the United States.
This is more than anything else from the letter kept in a private archive and now deposited in the Scientific Library of South Bohemia.
