A van with two thousand kilos of hash crosses the checkpoint in Alava
Five minus ten in the morning.
The officers summon the two occupants of a van to escape instead of stopping.
The officers summoned the two occupants of a van and instead of stopping they fled.
Their cargo, more than two tons of hashish, is a good reason not to stop.
The officers, after chasing them, manage to arrest one of the two occupants, a man of about 28 years, identified as A. A. J., according to a statement from the Interior Department of the Basque government.
