The Ministry of Interior requires drivers with three administrative penalties for excessive blood alcohol, install in his car the system that prevents driving the vehicle in a state of drunkenness or if he does not blow in the appropriate device.
The measure was announced last June and is already included in the annual report of the Attorney General’s Office, according to which it will be a pilot project lasting one year.
The aim of this project is the reinstatement of the driver, since this will have to attend a rehabilitation course on the road.
In addition to the General Prosecutor for Road Safety, the General Directorate of Traffic (DGT) and the Fondazione Tecnologico per la Seguridad dell’Automobile (FITSA) will participate in this initiative.
According to statistics, between 30% and 75% of drivers reported more than once per drunk driving then return to driving the car.
The alcoholic beverage would avoid it, because it is a system connected to the vehicle that measures the rate of alcohol in the exhaled air and prevents it from starting the car if the driver does not blow, or when a higher concentration of alcohol is detected than allowed.
The cost is over 1000 euros and would be borne by the sanctioned.
In this regard, a study conducted in the United States in 2007 showed that vehicles equipped with such devices can reduce up to 65% of the infringements committed during the first year of introduction.
And in Spain it is estimated that it could save the lives of 115 people a year.
The measure is limited to administrative penalties for two reasons: curbing these behaviors before they become criminal offenses.
And to facilitate its development, since legal reform can be carried out by ordinary means, and, undoubtedly, the necessary reform for the criminal procedure would require an organic law.
However, the device is not yet available on the Spanish market in any commercial solution, although it has already been introduced experimentally in some industrial and public vehicles.
