Industry prices continue to rise
The prices of domestic industrial sales in August 2008 increased by 0.1% compared to the previous month, by 12.9% compared to August 2007 - reports the Hungarian Central Institute of Statistics.
Industry export sales prices reported in July 2008 were 1.1% higher, compared to the previous year they decreased by 3.9%
As a result of the change in domestic and export prices, industrial production costs were 0.7% higher than the previous month and 3.2% higher than a year ago.
Industrial domestic sales prices reported in the previous month increased by only 0.1%.
Domestic sales prices in the manufacturing sector also rose to a minimal extent, by 0.1%, compared to July.
The biggest increase in prices in August 2008 occurred in the leather and shoes manufacturing sector (2.8%), especially bags and belts with 4.6% and shoe production with 2.5% monthly increase.
The high price level of plastic and chemical raw materials has caused a significant monthly increase (1.6%) in the product and chemical industry.
A decrease in prices occurred in the oil processing sector (1.4%), in the production of electric tools and machinery (0.9%) and to a minimum extent in woodworking (0.1%)
The prices of paper production, publishing and printing have not changed.
In the other sectors of the machining industry there was a price increase of between 0.2 and 0.9%.
In the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sector, prices rose in August by 0.3% in domestic industrial sales, primarily as a result of the dominant effect of the increase in gas prices by the authorities since 1 July.
Compared in 12 months, considering the domestic sales of the sectors of the processing industry, the largest increases were in the sector of the processing of petroleum products (32.4%).
In the manufacturing of metalworking products, the increase in prices was 13.2%, and 11% in the production of foodstuffs, beverages and tobacco was a determining factor.
A decrease in prices occurred in the textile sector (2.5%) and in the production of electric tools and machinery (0.3%).
In the other sectors of the machining industry the rate of price increase varied from 0.6% to 9.1%.
In total, prices in the manufacturing industry rose by 10.2% in the past year.
The prices of the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sector exceeded those of last year by 18.7%.
In domestic sales among the target groups of the sectors, the largest monthly price increase occurred in August in the sectors that produce investment goods (0.7%).
In the sectors that produce consumer goods prices have increased by 0.3%, in the energy sector and subsequent use prices have not changed compared to those of the previous month.
In August 2008, compared to the same month last year, the largest price increase was observed in the energy sector and subsequent use (16.8%).
In the sectors producing consumer goods the increase was 6.8%, for investment goods a decrease of 1.4% was measured.
The prices of industrial export sales calculated in florins increased in August by 1.1% compared to the previous month, compared to 12 months decreased by 3.9%.
