The European Summit on Equal Opportunities, organised this year by France as the rotating EU Presidency, began today in Paris.
Lívia Járóka, Member of the European People's Party Fidesz in the message addressed to the plenary as the main speaker of the congress drew attention to school segregation because it is the most serious legal violation affecting Roma children and, moreover, the most serious obstacle to their affirmation.
